-- Fortress to manage bad debt for Italian cooperative banks group 
-- By Francesca Landini
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 10:15AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 16 (Reuters) - Italian debt collector Italfondiario, controlled by U.S. asset manager Fortress Group <FIG.N>, has signed a partnership to manage problematic loans generated by a network of small Italian cooperative banks.

The deal marks an increasing involvement of Fortress in Italy. The U.S. group is also expected to sign a deal with UniCredit  <CRDI.MI> to buy the bank's debt collector unit UniCredit Credit Management Bank (UCCMB). [ID:nI6N0T002J]